cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for active learning with deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on image classification, object detection, and human pose estimation, which are all sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed involves a loss prediction module, which is a component of the neural network architecture and is learned through training, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method through experiments, which involves processing and analyzing data, making it relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves optimizing the performance of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under neural networks (cs.NE).
